    "Tony W. Cartledge": "). Some of the place names men-\ntioned\n(Shalishah,\nShaalim)\nare\nnow\nunidentifiable, and, for our purposes, beside the\npoint. The far-ranging attempts of some\nscholars to identify these obscure places provide\na modern metaphor for Saul\u2019s own search: a\nwandering, frustrating, and ultimately fruitless\nendeavor.\nSaul in Search of a Seer, 9:5-14\nBy the time their search had reached Zuph, Saul was ready to stop\nworrying about the donkeys lest his father start worrying about\nhim (",
